# 🏠 House Price Prediction using Machine Learning

## 📌 Overview
Predicts house prices using features like location, area, bedrooms, and condition to support real estate decision-making.

## 🎯 Problem Statement
Build a regression model to accurately estimate house prices based on historical data.

## 📊 Dataset
- KC House Dataset (~21K records, 21 features)

## ⚙️ Tech Stack
- Python, Pandas, NumPy  
- Scikit-learn  
- Matplotlib, Seaborn  
- Power BI  

## 🔍 Workflow
- Data Cleaning & Outlier Removal  
- Feature Engineering (Total Area, Renovation Flag, Zipcode Encoding)  
- Model Building (Linear Regression, Random Forest)  
- Evaluation (R², MAE, RMSE)  

## 📈 Performance
- Random Forest
- R² Score: **0.89**  
- MAE: ~69583.99 
- RMSE: ~124589.43 

## 📊 Insights
- grade ,zipcode strongly impacts price  
- Total house area → higher price  
- Renovated & waterfront houses cost more  

